<HR><H2>VEIL Protocol</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Sun Sep 10 22:55:30 1995
)</H3>
<PRE>
Date: Sun, 10 Sep 1995 20:54:59 -0600
From: 869683 Gillespie Brandon James &lt;brandon@smithfield.declab.usu.edu&gt;
To: coldstuff@MIT.EDU

The VEIL Protocol (Virtual Environment Interaction Layers Protocol) is
partially based off HTTP-NG, and is designed to give multiple i/o streams
over a single TCP connection.  The draft specification for VEIL is at:

    http://www.cold.org:8080/VEIL.html

Currently, the ColdX (ColdMUD) driver supports VEIL Packets (ColdX 1.0),
and a client is under development from the ColdX Project, written in python.


A list has been created to discuss VEIL and other Virtual Environment
System protocols:

    ves-protocols@tiny.mcs.usu.edu

Subscribe to it by emailing 'majordomo@tiny.mcs.usu.edu' with a message
body of 'subscribe ves-protocols'.

Enjoy!

-Brandon Gillespie/Lynx-
</PRE>
